data.text: @StephenSeiler @StephenSeiler Have you done a sport medical examination before your return?
@StephenSeiler Yes, what seems to be a "fly-and -die", not literally thank fully. Hope you're well on the mend.
@StephenSeiler That’s good. Maybe a bit of luck, but the other things likely also play a part.

@DrGwen23 To be honest, I have felt completely normal other than the 2-3 first days.  So, it seems I have been fortunate.  I have tried to sleep well, eat well and keep stress low and maybe that has helped a bit.

@StephenSeiler Try short hard intervals with longer recovery 
30 sec 150% CP
2 min recovery 
Repeat 10 X

@StephenSeiler actually put in my biggest week of the year when I was stuck at home after a positive test, ran 14 day I tested positive, 20 one week later, no abnormal breathing or heart rate issues. symptoms were mild headache days 1-3, sore throat days 1-2. Crazy how diff c-19 experiences are
@StephenSeiler I’d focus on cardiac response but respiratory a close 2nd.
